defs.name: TyParamBound
defs.docs:
The AST represents all type param bounds as types.
 `typeck::collect::compute_bounds` matches these against
 the "special" built-in traits (see `middle::lang_items`) and
 detects Copy, Send and Sync.

defs.name: TraitBoundModifier
defs.docs:
A modifier on a bound, currently this is only used for `?Sized`, where the
 modifier is `Maybe`. Negative bounds should also be handled here.

defs.name: WherePredicate

defs.name: Mac
defs.docs:
Represents a macro invocation. The Path indicates which macro
 is being invoked, and the vector of token-trees contains the source
 of the macro invocation.

defs.name: Delimited
defs.docs: A delimited sequence of token trees

defs.name: TokenTree
defs.docs:
When the main rust parser encounters a syntax-extension invocation, it
 parses the arguments to the invocation as a token-tree. This is a very
 loose structure, such that all sorts of different AST-fragments can
 be passed to syntax extensions using a uniform type.

defs.name: tts

defs.name: Path
defs.docs: A "Path" is essentially Rust's notion of a name.

defs.name: global
defs.docs:
A `::foo` path, is relative to the crate root rather than current
 module (like paths in an import).

defs.name: segments
defs.docs: The segments in the path: the things separated by `::`.

defs.name: PathSegment
defs.docs: A segment of a path: an identifier, an optional lifetime, and a set of types.

defs.name: ident
defs.docs: The identifier portion of this path segment.

defs.name: parameters
defs.docs:
Type/lifetime parameters attached to this path. They come in
 two flavors: `Path<A,B,C>` and `Path(A,B) -> C`. Note that
 this is more than just simple syntactic sugar; the use of
 parens affects the region binding rules, so we preserve the
 distinction.

defs.name: Parenthesized

defs.name: lifetimes
defs.docs: The lifetime parameters for this path segment.

defs.name: types
defs.docs: The type parameters for this path segment, if present.

defs.name: bindings
defs.docs: Bindings (equality constraints) on associated types, if present.

defs.name: TypeBinding
defs.docs: Bind a type to an associated type: `A=Foo`.

defs.name: QSelf
defs.docs:
The explicit Self type in a "qualified path". The actual
 path, including the trait and the associated item, is stored
 separately. `position` represents the index of the associated
 item qualified with this Self type.

defs.name: BareFnArg
defs.docs: An argument in a function type.

defs.name: visit
defs.docs:
AST walker. Each overridden visit method has full control over what
 happens with its node, it can do its own traversal of the node's children,
 call `visit::walk_*` to apply the default traversal algorithm, or prevent
 deeper traversal by doing nothing.

defs.name: Visitor
defs.docs:
Each method of the Visitor trait is a hook to be potentially
 overridden.  Each method's default implementation recursively visits
 the substructure of the input via the corresponding `walk` method;
 e.g. the `visit_mod` method by default calls `visit::walk_mod`.

defs.name: parse
defs.docs:
This module contains a set of exported nom parsers which can be used to
 parse custom grammars when used alongside the `synom` crate.
